title: HPI Spencer
content: The patient fell in October 2023, sustaining a left distal radius fracture. She was diagnosed with CRPS and has made progress but still cannot fully extend her wrist for activities like push-ups. Despite this, she continues Pilates without pain, making modifications as needed.

title: Musculoskeletal
content: Incision healing well, minimal scar, excellent finger motion without pain, supination, flexion to 45 degrees, extension to 20 degrees.

title: Imaging Results
content: X-rays show a well-healed fracture with hardware in place.

title: Plan
content: Review X-rays showing good plate alignment. Discuss limited motion for push-ups. Recommend advancing activities and follow-up in 3 months.
